verses.text:
I will punish my people because of all the evil things that they have done;
\q1 they have abandoned me and they offer offerings of worship to false gods.
\q2 They worship idols that they have made with their own hands!

It is as though everything in the sky is dismayed about what you have done;
\q2 it is as though they tremble and are very horrified. I, Yahweh, see and declare this to you.
\q1

You Israelite people, you were certainly not slaves when you were born;
\q2 so why were you captured by your enemies?
\q1

I looked and saw that the fields that previously were fertile had become a desert.
\q1 The cities were all ruined;
\q2 they had all been destroyed by Yahweh because he was extremely angry."

Then I thought, "We cannot expect these people to act righteously, because they are poor;
\q2 they do not have any sense.
\q1 They do not know the way Yahweh wants them to conduct their lives;
\q2 they do not know what God requires them to do.
\q1

People far north in the Israelite city of Dan can already hear the snorting of the horses of those who are preparing to attack us. It is as though the entire land is shaking as their army approaches;
\q they are coming to destroy our land and everything in it, the people and the cities."
\q

I will scatter them to many nations which neither they nor their ancestors have known anything about;
I will enable their enemies to strike them with swords until I have destroyed them."
\q

But Yahweh is the only true God;
\q2 he is the all-powerful God,
\q2 the king who rules forever.
\q1 When he is angry, all the earth shakes;
\q2 and the people of the nations cannot endure what he does when he is angry with them.
\b

Idols are worthless; they are just objects that make a mockery of the true God;
\q2 there will be a time when they all will be destroyed.
\q1

But the God whom we Israelites worship is not like those idols;
\q2 he is the one who created everything that exists;
\q1 we, the tribe of Israel, belong to him;
\q2 he is the commander of the angel armies.
\q1

It is as though our great tent is destroyed;
\q2 the ropes that held it up have been cut;
\q1 our children have gone away from us and will not return;
\q2 there are no people left to rebuild our great tent.
\q1

Yahweh, I know that no person controls what will happen to him;
\q2 no one is able to direct the events that he will experience.
\q1

The people in Judah are very distressed;
\q2 people are sitting on the ground and mourning;
\q1 in all of Jerusalem people are crying loudly.
\q1

You people have abandoned me;
\q2 you have continued to walk away from me.
\q1 So, I will lift up my fist to smash you;
\q2 I am tired of acting mercifully toward.
\q1

I said to my mother, "I am very sad;
\q1 I wish that you had not given birth to me;
\q2 everyone in this land opposes me and quarrels with me.
\q1 I have not made anyone angry by lending or borrow money and then quarreling about it,
\q2 but everyone curses me anyway."

Then I prayed, saying, "Yahweh, you are the one who strengthens me and protects me ;
\q2 you are the one to whom I go when I have troubles.
\q1 Some day people from nations all over the world will come to you and say,
\q2 'Our ancestors left us only something that was false;
\q1 they worshiped idols that are completely worthless .
\q1

Then Yahweh said, "Now I will show my power to the people of Judah;
\q2 I will show them that I am truly very powerful .
\q2 Then, finally, they will know that I, Yahweh, am the true God."

I have continually experienced much trouble and sorrow,
\q2 and I am disgraced now when I am about to die;
\q1 why was it necessary for me to me born?

I will punish you for your wicked deeds like you deserve to be punished;
\q1 It will be as though I will light a fire in your forests
\q2 that will burn up everything around you.'"

And Yahweh said to me, "Terrible things will happen to King Jehoahaz's brother, King Jehoiakim.
\q1 He unjustly forced men to build his palace.
\q2 The rooms on the upper level were built by men who were forced unjustly to do that work;
\q1 he forced his neighbors to work for nothing;
\q2 he did not pay them anything.
\q1

Yahweh says, "Even the priests and the prophets are ungodly;
\q2 they do wicked things even in his temple.
\q1

So, Yahweh will punish them; it will be like a great storm;
\q2 it will come down like a whirlwind, swirling around the heads of those wicked people.
\q1

Yahweh will punish your enemies;
\q2 it will be like a great storm;
\q2 it will come down like a whirlwind, swirling around the heads of wicked people.
\q1

You innocent people of Egypt,
\q2 go up to the region of Gilead to obtain medicine;
\q1 but it will be useless to take all those medicines;
\q2 you will not be healed.
\q1

The mercenaries that Egypt has hired are like fat calves because of the Egyptians' money;
\q2 but they also will turn around and run away;
\q1 they will not stand there and fight,
\q2 because it will be a day when there will be a great disaster for Egypt,
\q2 a day when their people will be greatly punished.
\q1

The people of Egypt will be humiliated;
\q2 they will be conquered by people from the northeast.'
\b

But it would not be right for their swords to stay there,
\q2 because Yahweh has commanded their enemies to do something more;
\q1 Yahweh intends to tell them to attack all the people living in Ashkelon and in other cities along the coast.

No one will boast about Moab again;
\q2 the enemies of Moab will plan to destroy the capital city, Heshbon.
\q2 They will say, 'Come, let us cause Moab to no longer be a nation.'
\q1 You also, You Madmen! you also will be silenced;
\q2 enemy armies will pursue you to kill you.
\q1

Listen to the people of Horonaim screaming;
\q2 they will be wailing because their town was completely destroyed .
\q1

All of Moab will be ruined;
\q2 even the little children will cry loudly.
\q1

The soldiers of Moab previously said, "We are warriors;
\q2 we have fought bravely in battles!"
\q1

Yahweh says, "The power of Moab will be finished;
\q2 it is as though it will have a broken arm.
\q1

We have all heard that the people of Moab are very proud;
\q2 they are extremely proud and conceited. 
\q1

All their enemies who found them attacked them.
\q2 They said, 'We did not sin by attacking them,
\q1 because they sinned against Yahweh;
\q2 he is the one who provides what they need;
\q1 he is the one to whom they should have remained faithful;
\q2 he is the one whom their ancestors confidently expected to help them.'
\b
\q1

Shout your battle cries throughout the land;
\q2 shout when you are causing great destruction.
\q1

The young men of Babylon will fall in the streets;
\q2 all their soldiers will be killed in one day. This will happen because I, Yahweh, have declared it!
\q1

Soon only jackals and other wild creatures will live there;
\q2 and it will be a place where ostriches live.
\q1 People will never live there again;
\q2 it will be uninhabited forever .
\q1

Their soldiers will fall dead in Babylonia;
\q2 they will die after being impaled by spears in the streets.
\q1

Yahweh, commander of the angel armies has solemnly promised, using his own name,
\q1 "Your cities will be filled with your enemies;
\q2 I will cause them to be like a swarm of locusts;
\q2 and they will shout triumphantly when they conquer your city."
\q1

People are as senseless as a beast, and they know very little;
\q1 those who make idols are always disappointed,
\q2 because their idols do nothing for them.
\q1 The images that they make are not real gods;
\q2 they are lifeless.
\q1

Idols are worthless; they deserve to be ridiculed;
\q2 there will be a time when they will all be destroyed.
\q1

But the God of Israel is not like those idols;
\q2 he is the one who created everything that exists;
\q1 we, the tribe of Israel, belong to him;
\q2 his name is Yahweh, commander of the angel armies.
\b
\q1

The people of Babylon will all roar like young lions;
\q2 they will growl like baby lions.
\q1
